<subSubSection id="269F6561DC67CD46FF0C80225565FCB1" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C80225153FD2F" blockId="30.[189,310,616,642]" box="[189,310,616,642]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="35728186DC67CD46FF0C80225153FD2F" bold="true" box="[189,310,616,642]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FF0C80225153FD2F" bold="true" box="[189,310,616,642]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C80DD5565FCB1" blockId="30.[188,1399,663,796]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Species in the 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FED980DD5221FD1C" box="[360,580,663,689]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alophoixi">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FED980DD5221FD1C" box="[360,580,663,689]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brueelia alophoixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group can be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FB5C80DD5537FD1C" authorityName="Keler" authorityYear="1936" box="[1261,1362,663,689]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FB5C80DD5537FD1C" box="[1261,1362,663,689]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brueelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: post-antennal head sensillum 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FBB080F0547EFD79" box="[1025,1051,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">s4</emphasis>
present (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC67CD46FB3980F05485FD78" box="[1160,1248,698,725]" captionStart="Figs 52–56" captionStartId="34.[189,241,1820,1846]" captionTargetBox="[374,1221,554,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-160@34.[360,1227,547,1778]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 52–56. Brueelia doisuthepensis sp. nov. 52. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 54. Male paramere, dorsal view. 55. Male mesosome, ventral view. 56. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; mts1–3 = marginal temporal seta 1–3; pmes = posterior mesosomal seta; pos = preocular seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; s4 = postantennal head sensillum 4; vms = vulval marginal setae; vos = vulval oblique setae; vss = vulval submarginal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358719/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
); thumb-like projection from the ventral carina into the clypeo-labral suture anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC67CD46FBAC80945410FD54" box="[1053,1141,734,761]" captionStart="Figs 52–56" captionStartId="34.[189,241,1820,1846]" captionTargetBox="[374,1221,554,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-160@34.[360,1227,547,1778]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 52–56. Brueelia doisuthepensis sp. nov. 52. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 54. Male paramere, dorsal view. 55. Male mesosome, ventral view. 56. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; mts1–3 = marginal temporal seta 1–3; pmes = posterior mesosomal seta; pos = preocular seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; s4 = postantennal head sensillum 4; vms = vulval marginal setae; vos = vulval oblique setae; vss = vulval submarginal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358719/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FB38809554C5FD55" box="[1161,1184,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">ss</emphasis>
present on female tergopleurite VIII (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC67CD46FE2A814B5197FCB1" box="[411,498,769,796]" captionStart="Figs 50–51" captionStartId="33.[189,241,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[390,1199,759,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-134@33.[385,1202,755,1884]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figs 50–51. Brueelia doisuthepensis sp. nov. 50. Male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 51. Female habitus, dorsal and ventral views. Abbreviations: aps = accessory post-spiracular seta; ps = paratergal seta; ss = sutural seta; sts = sternal seta; tps = tergal posterior seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358717/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
); lateral and median folds of the distal mesosome absent (
<figureCitation id="F6BE2A6FDC67CD46FB2A814B5497FCB1" box="[1179,1266,769,796]" captionStart="Figs 52–56" captionStartId="34.[189,241,1820,1846]" captionTargetBox="[374,1221,554,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-160@34.[360,1227,547,1778]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 52–56. Brueelia doisuthepensis sp. nov. 52. Male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53. Male genitalia, dorsal view. 54. Male paramere, dorsal view. 55. Male mesosome, ventral view. 56. Female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; mts1–3 = marginal temporal seta 1–3; pmes = posterior mesosomal seta; pos = preocular seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; s4 = postantennal head sensillum 4; vms = vulval marginal setae; vos = vulval oblique setae; vss = vulval submarginal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358719/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="269F6561DC67CD46FF0C8109525EFC21" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C81095267FCF0" blockId="30.[189,514,835,861]" box="[189,514,835,861]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="35728186DC67CD46FF0C81095267FCF0" bold="true" box="[189,514,835,861]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FF0C81095267FCF0" bold="true" box="[189,514,835,861]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C8138525EFC21" blockId="30.[189,571,882,909]" box="[189,571,882,909]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Africa, and South and 
<collectingCountry id="1692767ADC67CD46FE778139525DFC21" box="[454,568,882,909]" name="China" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">East Asia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="269F6561DC67CD46FF0C81FE5437FC53" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C81FE51F6FC63" blockId="30.[189,403,948,974]" box="[189,403,948,974]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="35728186DC67CD46FF0C81FE51F6FC63" bold="true" box="[189,403,948,974]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FF0C81FE51F6FC63" bold="true" box="[189,403,948,974]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Host associations</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C81A95437FC53" blockId="30.[189,1106,995,1022]" box="[189,1106,995,1022]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
All species except one are known from hosts in the 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FCAA81A953DEFC50" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[795,955,995,1021]" class="Aves" family="Pycnonotidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Pycnonotidae</taxonomicName>
(see below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="269F6561DC67CD46FF0C866F51A0FA61" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C866F514AFB92" blockId="30.[189,303,1061,1087]" box="[189,303,1061,1087]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading id="35728186DC67CD46FF0C866F514AFB92" bold="true" box="[189,303,1061,1087]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FF0C866F514AFB92" bold="true" box="[189,303,1061,1087]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C861E544AFAB2" blockId="30.[189,1399,1107,1312]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC67CD46FF0C861E5197FBC3" author="Mey E. &amp; Barker S. C." box="[189,498,1107,1134]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="73 - 114" refId="ref36334" refString="Mey E. &amp; Barker S. C. 2014. Eine neue auf den Feenvogeln (Irenidae) lebende Brueelia - Art (Insecta, Phthiraptera, Ischnocera, Philopteridae), nebst Anmerkungen zur Gattung Brueelia Keler, 1936 sensu lato. Rudolstadter Naturhistorische Schriften 19: 73 - 114." type="journal article" year="2014">Mey &amp; Barker (2014: 79)</bibRefCitation>
mention a 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FDCC86195321FBC0" authorityName="Ansari" authorityYear="1955" box="[637,836,1107,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guldum">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FDCC86195321FBC0" box="[637,836,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brueelia guldum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, which they defined as “narrowheaded”. No other species was included in this 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FD40863D532DFB3C" authorityName="Ansari" authorityYear="1955" box="[753,840,1143,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guldum">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FD40863D532DFB3C" box="[753,840,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">guldum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, which was only compared with species now placed in 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FEDA86D05247FB19" box="[363,546,1178,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Guimaraesiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FEDA86D05247FB19" box="[363,546,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Guimaraesiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above). 
<collectingRegion id="AC41F808DC67CD46FD0E86D1528EFB18" box="[703,747,1179,1205]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Not</collectingRegion>
all morphological characters defining the 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FB6F86D15512FB19" box="[1246,1399,1178,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alophoixi">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FB6F86D15512FB19" box="[1246,1399,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Br. alophoixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group can be seen in the illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FD4B86F5547EFB74" authority="Ansari, 1955" authorityName="Ansari" authorityYear="1955" box="[762,1051,1214,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guldum">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FD4B86F55319FB75" box="[762,892,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Br. guldum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC67CD46FC3386F4547EFB74" author="Ansari R. A. M." box="[898,1051,1214,1241]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="5 - 59" refId="ref34745" refString="Ansari R. A. M. 1955. Studies on the ischnoceron [sic] Mallophaga infesting birds in Pakistan. Proceedings of the Seventh Pakistan Scientific Conference, Biology, Bahawalpur 5 - 59." type="proceedings paper" year="1955">Ansari, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC67CD46FB9A86F454AAFB74" author="Ansari R. A. M." box="[1067,1231,1214,1241]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="46 - 62" refId="ref34814" refString="Ansari R. A. M. 1958 a. Studies on Ischnoceran Mallophaga infesting birds in the Panjab [Part I]. Indian Journal of Entomology 20: 46 - 62." type="journal article" year="1958">Ansari 1958a</bibRefCitation>
), and we only tentatively include this species in the 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FDCD86A85370FB51" box="[636,789,1250,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alophoixi">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FDCD86A85370FB51" box="[636,789,1250,1276]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Br. alophoixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. For this reason, we here refer to the group of 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FE98874F51EBFAB2" authorityName="Keler" authorityYear="1936" box="[297,398,1285,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FE98874F51EBFAB2" box="[297,398,1285,1311]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brueelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
living on bulbuls as the 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FD1F874C5323FAB2" box="[686,838,1285,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alophoixi">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FD1F874C5323FAB2" box="[686,838,1285,1311]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Br. alophoixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC67CD46FF0C870D51A0FA61" blockId="30.[189,1398,1351,1484]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The specimens of the 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FE0E870D52FEFACC" box="[447,667,1351,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Brueelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alophoixi">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FE0E870D52FEFACC" box="[447,667,1351,1377]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brueelia alophoixi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group included in the phylogeny of 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC67CD46FB15870D550BFACC" author="Bush S. E. &amp; Weckstein J. D. &amp; Gustafsson D. R. &amp; Allen J. &amp; DiBlasi E. &amp; Shreve S. M. &amp; Boldt R. &amp; Skeen H. R. &amp; Johnson K. P." box="[1188,1390,1351,1378]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="737 - 751" refId="ref34944" refString="Bush S. E., Weckstein J. D., Gustafsson D. R., Allen J., DiBlasi E., Shreve S. M., Boldt R., Skeen H. R. &amp; Johnson K. P. 2016. Unlocking the black box of feather louse diversity: a molecular phylogeny of the hyper-diverse genus Brueelia. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 94: 737 - 751. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2015.09.015" type="journal article" year="2016">
Bush 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FB598702557EFACC" box="[1256,1307,1351,1377]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al</emphasis>
. (2016
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3e, clade I-2) formed a monophyletic group with good support. This included both specimens from African and Asian hosts, reinforcing the morphological similarity among 
<taxonomicName id="A9854D69DC67CD46FBA987C454BCFA05" box="[1048,1241,1422,1448]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC67CD46FBA987C45418FA05" box="[1048,1149,1422,1448]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brueelia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from bulbuls in both faunal regions.
</paragraph>
